      <div class="themed-text-secondary leading-relaxed space-y-3">
        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Dimensionality uniqueness:</strong> The derivation shows three dimensions are necessary and sufficient. It does not show three is the unique solution. S<sup>2</sup> also embeds in ℝ<sup>4</sup>, ℝ<sup>5</sup>, etc. Does the framework structurally exclude higher-dimensional embeddings?</li>
